      • addBurningConditions

        public BurningConditions addBurningConditions(String date,
                                              int startTime,
                                              int endTime,
                                              double fwiGreater,
                                              double wsGreater,
                                              double rhLess,
                                              double isiGreater)
        Add a new set of burning conditions to the scenario.
        Parameters:
        date - The date that the condition is valid on. Must be formatted as 'YYYY-MM-DD'.
        startTime - The starting hour. Must be between 0 and 23 inclusive.
        endTime - The ending hour. Must be between 1 and 24 inclusive.
        fwiGreater - The minimum FWI value that will allow burning.
        wsGreater - The minimum wind speed that will allow burning.
        rhLess - The maximum relative humidity that will allow burning (as a percent [0-100]).
        isiGreater - The minimum ISI that will allow burning.
        Returns:

      • setFGMOptions

        public void setFGMOptions(Duration maxAccTs,
                          double distRes,
                          double perimRes,
                          double minSpreadRos,
                          boolean stopAtGridEnd,
                          boolean breaching,
                          boolean dynamicSpatialThreshold,
                          boolean spotting,
                          boolean purgeNonDisplayable,
                          boolean growthPercentileApplied,
                          double growthPercentile)
        Set the FGM options.
        Parameters:
        maxAccTs - The maximum time step during acceleration.
        distRes - The distance resolution.
        perimRes - The perimeter resolution.
        minSpreadRos - Minimum Spreading ROS.
        stopAtGridEnd - Whether to stop the fire spread when the simulated fire reaches the boundary of the grid data.
        breaching - Whether breaching is turned on or off.
        dynamicSpatialThreshold - Whether using the dynamic spatial threshold algorithm is turned on or off.
        spotting - Whether the spotting model should be activated.
        purgeNonDisplayable - Whether internal/hidden time steps are retained.
        growthPercentileApplied - Whether the growth percentile value is applied.
        growthPercentile - Growth percentile, to apply to specific fuel types.

      • setProbabilisticValues

        public void setProbabilisticValues(double dx,
                                   double dy,
                                   Duration dt)
        How much to nudge ignitions to perform probabilistic analyses on ignition location and start time. Primarily used when ignition information is not 100% reliable.
        Parameters:
        dx - How much to nudge ignitions to perform probabilistic analyses on ignition location.
        dy - How much to nudge ignitions to perform probabilistic analyses on ignition location.
        dt - How much to nudge ignitions to perform probabilistic analyses on ignition location and start time.

      • setFWIOptions

        public void setFWIOptions(boolean fwiSpatialInterp,
                          boolean fwiFromSpatialWeather,
                          boolean historyOnEffectedFWI,
                          boolean burningConditionsOn,
                          boolean fwiTemporalInterp)
        Set the FWI options.
        Parameters:
        fwiSpatialInterp - Apply spatial interpolation to FWI values.
        fwiFromSpatialWeather - Calculate FWI values from temporally interpolated weather.
        historyOnEffectedFWI - Apply history to FWI values affected by patches, grids, etc..
        burningConditionsOn - Use burning conditions.
        fwiTemporalInterp - Apply spatial interpolation to FWI values.
